   103	Concrete mechanism: the lint unconditionally converts forced entity-contained answer occurrences into `waived_forced_substring` and makes `green` depend only on other findings ([nlb_lint.py lines 191–209](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_lint.py:191), [lines 268–278](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_lint.py:268)). G3 ignores whether the waived list is nonempty. The only model-arm protection is prose in `a5-nl.design.n_planned.successors` ([line 35](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:35)).
   104	
   105	Why it matters: a model-based successor reusing this lint can receive a green receipt with all 28 leaks unless a human remembers the caveat. The current non-model result is not directly biased by surface answer extraction—the deterministic gazetteer uses longest, non-overlapping entity matches and the engine computes the answers—but the reuse guard is not fail-closed.
