    47	## 0. What this experiment is — and is not
    48	
    49	The parents banked, per vertical, an audited instrument-adequacy PASS on
    50	*gold-parsed* closed-grammar queries against the engine:
    51	
    52	- PREMISE: l3a engine covered exactness 600/600 (one-sided Wilson 95% LB
    53	  0.9955) and strict-code refusal 300/300 (LB 0.9911), audit CONFIRMED
    54	  [MEASURED: registry/verdicts/l3a.json].
    55	- PREMISE: a5 engine covered exactness 855/855 (LB 0.9968) and strict-code
    56	  refusal 122/122 (LB 0.9783), audit CONFIRMED
    57	  [MEASURED: registry/verdicts/a5.json].
    58	- PREMISE: both parent verdicts extrapolate to NO natural-language behaviour
    59	  — verbatim in both envelopes [MEASURED: the two verdict
    60	  `extrapolation_envelope_verbatim` fields].
    61	
    62	This record pair tests the NEXT pre-declared stage and nothing else: **can a
    63	deterministic NL front-end (mapper `a1-hybrid` + entity gazetteer + closed
    64	frame layer) replace the gold parse on the SAME frozen eval queries against
    65	the same engine (G2-verified parent-identical behaviour — §10.9), at a
    66	pre-declared maximum loss, without breaking the fail-closed contract?** HL3a clause 2 verbatim (frozen in l3a):
    67	*"mapper-parse loses > a pre-declared fraction of gold-parse accuracy (the NL
    68	boundary eats the rung; L3 waits for a better parser, not more GPU)"* — this
    69	record instantiates that clause (and its HA5 analog) with the pre-declared
    70	fraction set in §6.
    71	
    72	It is NOT: an LLM experiment (no model anywhere — R0), a cost-ratio or
    73	engine-vs-LLM claim (successors `l3a-cost` / `a5-llm`), a natural-user-
    74	distribution NL-robustness claim (phrasings are agent-authored under a blind
    75	protocol — §5, ASM-0140), or a real-world coverage claim.
    76	
    77	## 1. Hypotheses
    78	
    79	- **H-NLB-L3 (family/world vertical, record `l3a-parse`):** the deterministic
    80	  front-end retains ≥ 0.90 of gold-parse covered exactness on the frozen l3a
    81	  eval (equivalently, absolute covered-exact rate > 0.90 — the gold ceiling
    82	  is MEASURED at 1.0, so retained fraction ≡ absolute rate; see §6), while
    83	  keeping the fail-closed contract (controls refused; mis-parses become
    84	  refusals, not wrong answers).
    85	- **H-NLB-A5 (code vertical, record `a5-nl`):** the same, on the frozen a5
    86	  eval, with the same engine + `kot_code` desugaring layer.
    87	
    88	Falsifiable both ways: FAIL fires the parent kill clause verbatim
    89	("L3 waits for a better parser, not more GPU"); PASS licenses only the §8
    90	envelope.
    91	
    92	## 2. Registered forks (design-space uncertainties, never silently decided)
    93	
    94	| Fork | Options | Decision + why | Re-opens when |
    95	|---|---|---|---|
    96	| **FK-NLB-1** record topology | (a) one record, vertical as IV; (b) two records, one shared harness | **(b).** The frozen parents each pre-declare a SEPARATE successor id gated on their own verdict; the two kills (HL3a clause 2 / HA5 NL analog) must be able to fire independently; pooling verticals would smuggle a cross-vertical average into a per-vertical kill. Shared harness + shared analysis helper, pinned byte-identically in both records. | never (frozen parents bind) |
    97	| **FK-NLB-2** primary floor | 0.80 / 0.90 / 0.95 | **0.90** (§6 justification). Genuinely uncertain where "reachable" flips; 0.90 is decidable at both frozen n and instantiates the clause-2 "pre-declared fraction" at 10% max loss. | a measured point in (0.80, 0.90) → INCONCLUSIVE re-opens the fork WITH data |
    98	| **FK-NLB-3** front-end class | deterministic-only (mapper a1-hybrid + gazetteer + closed frames) vs LLM-assisted parse | **deterministic-only.** Clause 2 is ABOUT the deterministic boundary; an LLM parser re-imports stochasticity ahead of the determinism pitch and is the pre-declared SUCCESSOR if the kill fires. | kill fires |
    99	| **FK-NLB-4** phrasings per query | K=1 / K=3 | **K=1** held-out phrasing per eval query: keeps n identical to the parents' powered slices, keeps items independent (K=3 clusters), keeps cost ~$10. Paraphrase-diversity is enforced by quota (§5) instead of by K. | a PASS→ paraphrase-robustness successor may use K>1 |
   100	| **FK-NLB-5** malformed stratum | render as gibberish NL vs exclude | **exclude.** Malformedness is a property of the structured query; it has no faithful NL rendering, and the parents already banked shape-validation. Control n becomes 270 (l3a) / 106 (a5). Registered scope cut. | never for this pair |
   101	| **FK-NLB-6** control refusal scoring | strict engine code (parents') vs pipeline-acceptable set | **pipeline-acceptable**: refused with {the pre-authored expected engine code} ∪ {ERR_PARSE}. Under an NL front-end the refusal may legitimately fire EARLIER (e.g. unknown-entity → gazetteer miss → ERR_PARSE, never reaching the engine's ERR_UNKNOWN_ENTITY). Strict engine-code match is reported descriptively. The dangerous direction (control ANSWERED) is what the gate must exclude. | never |
   102	| **FK-NLB-7** refusal-gate level per record | 0.95 both / 0.95 + 0.90 | **l3a-parse 0.95; a5-nl 0.90.** At a5's frozen control n=106 (after FK-NLB-5) a 0.95 gate is UNDECIDABLE under the Holm-worst-case bound (even 105/106 observed fails; only a perfect 106/106 passes — a gate that only a perfect score can pass fails the P8 §1.6 lint). 0.90 at n=106 passes from 102/106 (§7). Registered asymmetry, driven by n, not by preference. | a5 control set ever grows |
   103	| **FK-NLB-8** paraphrase discipline (FREEZE-CANDIDATE fork, amends the draft §5 quota) | forced ≥50% no-label quota / syntactic-diversity quotas + descriptive no-label probe | **quotas + probe.** The mapper lexicon is single-label-per-concept with a rule lemmatizer and no synonym table [MEASURED: mapper/src/lexicon.ts + mapper/src/lemmatize.ts; probe runs 2026-07-10 — "who gave birth to X" maps give+birth not mother, "makers of"/"parts of" map nothing], so no-label phrasings are unmappable BY CONSTRUCTION and a forced 50% no-label stratum would predetermine FAIL arithmetically and break the §7 planning-value decidability the design binds itself to. Replaced by: free natural use of the relation's name + mechanically linted syntactic-diversity quotas (≥ min(6, n) distinct masked templates per covered family; no template > 50%; canonical scaffold ≤ 50%) + a 60-item/vertical no-label synonym PROBE, descriptive only, never gated, carved out of the envelope. Label-verbatim vs paraphrase stratification stays a reported endpoint. [STIPULATED: ASM-0144] | a parser-investment successor adds a synonym/alias layer (new record id) |
   104	| **FK-NLB-9** DEV-set basis (FREEZE-CANDIDATE fork, amends the draft §5.3) | DEV sampled from scored eval queries, disjoint author identities / DEV over FRESH identities disjoint from every scored item | **fresh-disjoint.** DEV = 60 designer-authored phrasings per vertical over freshly minted entities (`data/nlb-phrasings-*/dev-entities.jsonl`) absent from both world stores and every eval item (linted, DEV-FRESH); DEV items are never scored; the dev-pass gazetteer augmentation never enters a scored arm. Item-level disjointness replaces author-identity separation for DEV: with the front-end pinned before any EVAL phrasing exists, designer-DEV has no channel into the blind EVAL distribution and its only failure mode LOWERS the primary (conservative). EVAL/PROBE authoring keeps the full fresh-identity blind protocol. [STIPULATED: ASM-0145] | never for this pair; the skeptic re-attack (§11 item 6) attacks it against the built corpus |
   105	
   106	## 3. The pipeline under test (one shared harness)
   107	
   108	```
   109	NL phrasing (held-out, blind-authored)
   110	  → [1] entity gazetteer     (deterministic longest-match over surface text;
   111	                              built from the pinned world stores' entity URN
   112	                              slugs + declared surface variants; ambiguity or
   113	                              miss → ERR_PARSE/gazetteer-miss)
   114	  → [2] mapper a1-hybrid     (@jeswr/kernel-mapper, policyPreset('a1-hybrid'),
   115	                              policy sha e13dc838… pinned; lexicon compiled
   116	                              from the PINNED manifests: kernel-v0 +
   117	                              molecules-v0 for l3a-parse; + code-v0 for a5-nl;
   118	                              abstention in a required slot → ERR_PARSE/mapper-abstain)
   119	  → [3] closed frame layer   (deterministic rule set: wh/op keywords → op +
   120	                              direction; exactly one mapped concept URN fills
   121	                              the rel/concept slot; 0 or ≥2 → ERR_PARSE/frame-miss)
   122	  → kot-query/1 (l3a-parse) or kot-query-code/1 (a5-nl)
   123	  → engine                   (tools/axiom/kot_axiom.py sha d2640881…;
   124	                              + tools/axiom/kot_code.py sha 9fbe2a50… for a5-nl.
   125	                              kot_code is byte-identical to the frozen parent
   126	                              pin; kot_axiom is NOT — the define-op line
   127	                              extended it post-parent-freeze, so behavioural
   128	                              identity on the parent evals is re-verified
   129	                              IN-RUN by gate G2 instead of asserted
   130	                              [STIPULATED: ASM-0147]. The engine is NOT
   131	                              modified by this experiment.)
   132	```
   133	
   134	**Frame-layer closed knowledge (finalised on DEV, pinned):** the frame layer
   135	carries (i) a per-relation surface-orientation table `ROLE_DIR` — which
   136	engine direction realises the role reading "the R of E" for the five
   137	relations with world edges (mother/father forward; maker-of, part-of
   138	inverse; has-part forward); every other relation defaults to a direction the
   139	engine refuses fail-closed; (ii) a label-variant matcher over the mapped
   140	concept's OWN label (inflections + the closed two-irregular table
   141	made→make, children→child); (iii) the closed a5 op-keyword cascade; and
   142	(iv) a fail-closed op default: inverse-possessive shapes parse as `lookup`
   143	(the set-valued, non-guessing op) unless the phrasing carries an explicit
   144	exactly-one marker — a `unique` guess on a set-valued family would fabricate
   145	a scalar answer (an S2 wrong answer), which is exactly what the front-end
   146	must never do. The frame layer performs **NO concept aliasing** ("made" maps
   147	to the distinct `make` concept and dies at the engine as a safe refusal, not
   148	a rescue): the mapper stays the sole concept-binding component, so stage
   149	indictment and the G5 derangement stay clean. All of this is grammar-like
   150	closed knowledge, none of it answer knowledge. [STIPULATED: ASM-0146]
   151	
   152	Fail-closed contract of the front-end: every non-parse is a **refusal** with
   153	code `ERR_PARSE` and a stage tag (`gazetteer-miss` | `mapper-abstain` |
   154	`frame-miss` | `frame-ambiguous`); the front-end NEVER guesses a slot. Stage
   155	distribution is reported descriptively (architecture-ladder §8 item 14 stage
   156	indictment: a FAIL must say WHICH stage ate the rung).
   157	
   158	Honesty note (registered): on the code vertical the mapper's lexicon leg is
   159	thin — the seven relational ops are carried by frame keywords + identifier
   160	gazetteer, and the mapper's concept mapping decides only the `instance-of`
   161	concept slot. a5-nl therefore stresses frame+entity-linking more than
   162	lexicon mapping; l3a-parse stresses lexicon mapping (relation/concept words).
   163	Together they cover the boundary; separately each licenses only its vertical.
   164	
   165	The frame layer's rule set is **DRAFT until freeze**: it may be revised
   166	against the blind DEV phrasing set only (§5), then its sha256 is pinned in
   167	the record BEFORE the held-out eval phrasings are authored (ordering is part
   168	of the blindness protocol, §5/§10).
   169	
