   197	## 5. Blind phrasing protocol (the load-bearing input discipline)
   198	
   199	Authoring identities and blindness:
   200	
   201	1. **Phrasing authors** are FRESH agent identities (not the designer, not the
   202	   front-end author, not the runner) invoked with a PINNED prompt
   203	   (`data/nlb-phrasings-*/prompt-eval.md`) whose context contains ONLY, per
   204	   query, the AUTHOR PACKET line (`tools/experiments/nlb/gen_author_packets.py`,
   205	   deterministic): a semantic SHAPE id (op + which side of the relation the
   206	   entity sits on — rendered via the same closed orientation semantics the
   207	   eval was authored under), the relation/concept LABEL (e.g. "mother",
   208	   "maker of", "python function"), and the entity LABEL — the URN slug
   209	   verbatim (the entity's canonical and ONLY name; hyphens may be written as
   210	   spaces; a5 identifiers are used verbatim, e.g.
   211	   `code-fn-claims-check--check-doc`, because the identifier IS the name).
   212	   FREEZE-CANDIDATE strengthening over the draft: packets carry NO family
   213	   name and NO covered/control class — controls are phrased faithfully as
   214	   questions without the author knowing they are controls. Authors get NO
   215	   repo access, NO mapper lexicon, NO front-end code, NO expected answers,
   216	   NO other line's output. One fresh identity per 100-packet batch;
   217	   transcripts committed.
   218	2. **Blind-to-lexicon** (the memo's required attack, §10.1): authors cannot
   219	   tune phrasings to mappable surface forms because they never see which
   220	   forms map. Since relation LABELS are themselves lexicon surface forms
   520	
   521	**10.5 Gate decidability / brittleness.** All gates shown passable-and-
   522	failable at frozen n (§7). The one brittle candidate found (a5 S1 at 0.95,
   523	undecidable at n=106 under Holm worst case) was repaired by FK-NLB-7 BEFORE
   524	freeze rather than discovered after. Malformed exclusion (FK-NLB-5) removes
   525	the one stratum whose NL rendering would be undecidable-by-construction.
   526	
   527	**10.6 Mock contamination.** Mock scaffold phrasings live under
   528	`poc/nlb-mock/`, never under `data/`; G3's manifest pins the authored corpus
   529	only; authoring identities never receive mock text (§5.6). A grep-lint in G3
   530	additionally rejects any eval phrasing byte-identical to a mock template
   531	instantiation.
   532	
   533	**10.7 Envelope overreach (the m0b lesson).** The tempting headline "NL
   534	reaches the kernel's checker" is NOT licensed by K=1 agent-authored
   535	phrasings on two self-authored verticals; §8's carve-outs are verbatim in
   536	both records, and the per-vertical licensing split blocks a silent
   537	conjunction claim.
   538	
   539	**10.8 Designer-authored DEV (freeze-candidate attack).** Threat: the
   540	designer (who has read the lexicon and the mapper) authors the DEV set and
   541	tunes the frame on it — could that inflate the primary? Channel analysis:
   542	inflation requires the DEV distribution to predict the EVAL distribution's
   543	*idiosyncrasies*; EVAL phrasings do not exist at tuning time and are later
   544	authored blind by fresh identities from packets the designer's phrasings
   545	never touch, and DEV items are over fresh entities never scored anywhere
   546	(linted). What designer-DEV *can* do is fit the frame to unrepresentative
   547	syntax — which shows up as EVAL misses, i.e. LOWERS the primary
   548	(conservative). The symmetric attack (designer authors deliberately easy DEV
   549	so G4 passes while the artifact is broken) is bounded by G4's role: it is an
   550	instrument gate, not evidence for the primary; a broken front-end still
   551	fails on EVAL where it counts. Residual risk registered as ASM-0145; the
   552	non-designer skeptic re-attacks this against the BUILT corpus before freeze.
   553	
   554	**10.9 Engine drift since the parents froze.** The define-op line extended
   555	`kot_axiom.py` after the parents' freeze, so the "byte-identical engine"
   556	premise of the draft is FALSE at head. Repair: the records pin the engine
   557	that actually runs (sha d2640881…) and make behavioural identity on the
   558	parent surface an EXECUTABLE in-run gate — G2 must reproduce the
   559	parent-perfect 600/600+300/300 and 855/855+122/122 on the byte-identical
   560	parent evals/stores, and G2 failure is INSTRUMENT-INVALID while G2 success
   561	is a PASS conjunct. Measured green on the 2026-07-10 mock receipts
   562	[STIPULATED: ASM-0147]. A byte-identity claim that is not re-verified would
   563	have been weaker than this gate.
   564	
   565	Skeptic conclusion: with G2–G6 + the §5 ordering protocol in place, the
   566	remaining unmitigated risks are ASM-0140 (agent-authored proxy), ASM-0145
   567	(designer-DEV, conservative direction), ASM-0147 (engine continuity via G2)
   568	and the inherited parent stipulations — all registered, none load-bearing
   569	for the verdict function itself. CLEAR TO PROCEED TO FREEZE once §11 items
   570	1–6 are green. (This memo attacks the DESIGN; the pre-freeze skeptic pass
   571	must be re-run by a non-designer identity against the BUILT inputs.)
