   722	### 14.3 Recoverability-audit gate: split + extension (amends §5.5)
   723	
   724	- DECISION: the audit gate is the SHAPE+ENTITY recovery rate over a 60-item
   725	  COVERED-only in-scope sample, gate ≥ 0.95 (≥ 57/60). Rel/concept-label
   726	  recovery and control-item recovery become DESCRIPTIVE. Rationale: the
   727	  gate's registered purpose is answerability (a FAIL must not be
   728	  manufacturable by unanswerable phrasings); shape+entity carries that.
   729	  Gating on label recovery under stem-overlap would force label-verbatim
   730	  authoring through the back door — re-imposing what FK-NLB-8
   731	  registered-removed — and double-counts the synonym penalty that the
   732	  experiment itself measures (label-verbatim stratification + probe).
   733	  Controls are insensitive to shape recovery in the dangerous direction
   734	  (any parse of an out-of-scope/unknown item still refuses).
   735	  [STIPULATED: ASM-0421]
