   852	### 14.7 Scorer enrichment ratification (2026-07-10) — unblocks §14.6 step 2
   853	
   854	Author: Kern (Fable designer role), adjudicating the runner's blocker from
   855	the §14.6 partial. Amends the §14.6 change-list (items 2 and 5 as edited
   856	above); everything else in §14 stands.
   857	
   858	- PREMISE: §14.6 step 2 needs the S2 numerator restricted to the 7
   859	  in-scope families and a per-family descriptive `shape_ambiguous_stratum`,
   860	  but the pinned instrument's `score_nl` emits `by_family` as `{n, ok}`
   861	  only (ok = exact on covered families), so neither quantity is derivable
   862	  from the pinned emission plus run totals; substituting the run-level
   863	  `n_covered_answered_wrong` would rest on the contingent fact that the
   864	  dropped families abstained — the manufactured-kill pathway §14.1
   865	  preempts, should that fact ever fail on a re-run
   866	  [MEASURED: runner build report, commit
   867	  0847ce079189b4d1244911fe026b0799e1db4da7; pre-EVAL instrument pin
   868	  426722aa813a7843190849348a6b309f3e898d19a0b979f354d5207dc85c6073].
   869	- DECISION (ratifies the runner-proposed fix): `score_nl.by_family` gains
   870	  four ADDITIVE per-family covered-outcome buckets
   871	  `{exact, wrong, refused_parse, refused_engine}` — a pure re-bucketing of
   872	  outcomes score_nl already classifies, each bucket incremented on exactly
   873	  the branch of its existing run-level counterpart; `n`/`ok` semantics
   874	  unchanged; buckets stay zero on control families; no parse, outcome,
   875	  phrasing, or front-end behaviour changes; frame files stay byte-frozen.
   876	  Extends the ASM-0424 lawful scorer-side edit set by this one named,
   877	  diff-scoped edit and no other [STIPULATED: ASM-0480].
   878	
   879	Outcome→bucket mapping (covered items; each row is the SAME branch as its
   880	run-level twin — no new predicate exists):
   881	
   882	| bucket | increments when | run-level twin |
   883	|---|---|---|
   884	| `exact` | status=answer AND value==expected AND (mapper/deranged arms) provenance⊆world + license non-empty | `n_covered_exact` (== `ok` on covered) |
   885	| `wrong` | status=answer AND not exact | `n_covered_answered_wrong` |
   886	| `refused_parse` | status≠answer AND code==ERR_PARSE | `n_covered_refused_parse` |
   887	| `refused_engine` | status≠answer AND code≠ERR_PARSE (incl. policy ABSTAIN on the abstain-all arm, mirroring the run total) | `n_covered_refused_engine` |
   888	
   889	Invariants (mechanically checkable, folded into G1 per the step-2 spec
   890	below): per covered family `exact + wrong + refused_parse + refused_engine
   891	== n` and `exact == ok`; summed over the 9 covered families each bucket
   892	equals its run-level twin; control families hold zeros and keep `ok` =
   893	acceptable-refusal.
   894	
   895	- Lawfulness: `score_nl` runs strictly AFTER `run_nl_arm` has produced
   896	  every outcome; it neither parses nor answers, so the edit cannot leak
   897	  eval content into the system under test. The §14.5 blindness invariant
   898	  is carried by nlb_frontend.py, nlb_map.mjs, the mapper policy pin and
   899	  the phrasing bytes — all byte-untouched (diff confined to `score_nl`;
   900	  `run_nl_arm`, `fabricate`, oracle construction and the parse invocation
   901	  byte-unchanged). The G6 determinism gate compares outcomes, not metrics,
   902	  so it is unaffected. ASM-0424's enumeration named the lint/analysis
   903	  scripts but not the instrument's aggregation function; ASM-0480 closes
   904	  that gap for this single edit — any OTHER nlb_instrument.py edit still
   905	  mints a new record id.
