   274	
   275	## 6. Endpoints (EXACTLY ONE primary per record) and verdict rules
   276	
   277	All bounds: one-sided Wilson (kot_common formula), z = 1.645 for primary and
   278	kill rules; the two gated secondaries form ONE Holm family per record
   279	(step-down over their one-sided p-values at family α = 0.05; the analysis
   280	script exports booleans, §6.3).
   281	
   282	### 6.1 Primary (per record) — retained covered exactness, non-inferiority form
   283	
   284	`/analysis/retained_covered_exact_wilson_lb` — one-sided Wilson 95% LB of the
   285	**mapper-parse arm's covered-exact rate** over the SAME covered queries the
   286	parent froze (l3a-parse n=527 — the FK-NLB-10 shape-recoverable in-scope
   287	slice of the 600 executed, §14.2; a5-nl n=855), scored EXACTLY as the parent
   288	(status=answer ∧ value=expected ∧ provenance⊆world-ids ∧ license≠∅), tested
   289	against **floor 0.90**.
   290	
   291	- **Retained-fraction ≡ absolute rate, by measurement:** the gold ceiling is
   292	  MEASURED at 600/600 and 855/855 [registry/verdicts/l3a.json, a5.json], so
   293	  the retained fraction's denominator is the full n — the F2
   294	  degenerate-denominator lesson is discharged by construction, and the
   295	  primary is stated in absolute non-inferiority form (margin δ = 0.10 vs the
   296	  measured ceiling 1.0). No TOST upper leg exists (the pipeline cannot exceed
   297	  its own gold ceiling); the one-sided NI bound IS the equivalence machinery.
   298	- **Floor justification (from the parents' measured baselines):** the parents
   299	  gate the instrument at 0.98 (covered) / 0.95 (refusal); their measured
   300	  ceilings are 1.0. Floor 0.90 = measured ceiling − 0.10, instantiating HL3a
   301	  clause 2's "pre-declared fraction" at **10% maximum NL-boundary loss** —
   302	  the level at which the pipeline still answers ≥9/10 covered NL queries
   303	  exactly while every miss is (separately gated) a refusal, not a wrong
   304	  answer. Below it, the exactness premium the engine leg banked stops being
   305	  the pipeline's property, and the pre-declared programme response is parser
   306	  investment, not GPU (kill text verbatim). The 10% number itself is a
   307	  programme POLICY choice, registered as ASM-0141 (STIPULATED), with
   308	  FK-NLB-2 re-opening on an INCONCLUSIVE landing.
   309	- Planning value 0.95 → LB 0.9320 (l3a-parse, n=527 — FK-NLB-10 re-scope,
   310	  §14.2) / 0.9363 (a5-nl, n=855; the draft's 0.9351 was corrected at the
   311	  freeze-candidate recomputation, §7): clears the floor; passes the P8 §1.6
   312	  decidability lint (§7).
   313	
   314	### 6.2 Gated secondaries (one Holm family per record; m = 2)
   315	
   316	- **S1 — control refusal retention:** rate of included control queries
   317	  (l3a 270 / a5 106) refused with an ACCEPTABLE code — the pre-authored
   318	  expected engine code or `ERR_PARSE` (FK-NLB-6) — gate **> 0.95 (l3a-parse)
   319	  / > 0.90 (a5-nl)** (FK-NLB-7). Strict engine-code match and refused-any are
   320	  reported descriptively.
   321	- **S2 — the dangerous half of the fail-closed split:** covered
   322	  **mis-parse→wrong-answer rate** (status=answer ∧ value≠expected, any arm
   323	  stage) — one-sided Wilson UB gate **< 0.02**. A wrong answer under NL parse
   324	  carries provenance and license strings and is therefore WORSE than a
   325	  refusal (false authority); it gets its own gate rather than riding the
   326	  primary. The safe half (mis-parse→refusal) is the primary's complement and
   327	  is reported by stage (descriptive).
   328	
   329	### 6.3 Instrument gates (each with its own bound; any failure ⇒ INSTRUMENT-INVALID)
   330	
   331	- **G1** arm presence + per-stratum counts match the manifest (600/270,
   332	  855/106 + dev 60).
   333	- **G2 gold-replication:** the gold-parse arm re-runs the parent's FULL eval
   334	  (incl. malformed) on the engine that actually runs (§10.9) and must reproduce the
   335	  parent-perfect outcome (l3a 600/600 covered + 300/300 strict-code control;
   336	  a5 855/855 + 122/122) — the ceiling is re-verified in-run, not assumed.
   337	- **G3 phrasing-corpus lints + blindness artifacts** (§5.4): manifest hash
   338	  match, one-per-qid, no-URN/grammar/answer leakage, transcripts + pinned
   339	  prompt + recoverability-audit record present.
   340	- **G4 dev-set front-end abstention ≤ 0.20** (≤12/60) — the mapper-abstention
   341	  instrument bound. On the DEV set the front-end was allowed to iterate, so
   342	  exceeding 0.20 there means the shipped artifact is broken/pin-drifted, not
   343	  that NL is hard. On the EVAL set abstention is SUBSTANCE (it lowers the
   344	  primary and is reported by stage) — deliberately NOT an instrument gate, so
   345	  the experiment cannot dodge the kill by declaring itself invalid.
   346	- **G5 deranged-lexicon leakage guard:** the deranged arm (§6.4) must retain
   347	  covered exactness **< 0.10**; otherwise the eval is answerable without
   348	  correct concept mapping (frame/entity shape alone) and the instrument—not
   349	  the mapper—is generating the signal ⇒ INSTRUMENT-INVALID.
   350	- **G6 determinism:** full mapper-parse pass run twice, byte-identical.
   351	
   352	### 6.4 Arms (per record)
   353	
   354	| Arm | Role |
   355	|---|---|
   356	| `mapper-parse` | the pipeline under test (§3) |
   357	| `gold-replication` | measured ceiling + G2 regression check (parent's gold queries) |
   358	| `deranged-lexicon` | scramble control: seed-pinned fixed-point-free permutation of the front-end's semantic bindings — concept-URN targets (l3a-parse); op→op derangement + concept targets (a5-nl, because its op keywords carry the relational semantics). Analog of the mandatory shuffled-kernel control at R0: correct concept BINDING, not pipeline shape, must carry the result. |
   359	| `abstain-all` | trivial policy: refuses every phrasing (perfect refusal, zero exactness) |
   360	| `answer-all` | trivial policy: never refuses (parent fabrication policy on parsed queries; deterministic global default on parse failures) — high-answer/zero-refusal bracket |
   361	
   362	The kernel-as-text null is NOT instantiable here (no model consumes anything
   363	— R0, no host; same registered adaptation as the frozen parents, which the
   364	parents' records carry in `arms_mandatory_baselines`). The two trivial
   365	policies + deranged arm are the registered null/scramble set.
   366	
   367	### 6.5 Verdict rules (per record, mechanical)
   368	
   369	1. **INSTRUMENT-INVALID** iff NOT `/gates/instrument_valid` (G1–G6).
   370	2. **FAIL** iff `/analysis/retained_covered_exact_wilson_ub` ≤ floor(0.90)
   371	   **OR** `/analysis/covered_wrong_answer_wilson_lb` ≥ 0.02 (fail-closed
   372	   demonstrably broken — the second, independent way the NL boundary kills
   373	   the rung). Kill text inherited verbatim from the parent (§1).
   374	3. **PASS** iff `/analysis/retained_covered_exact_wilson_lb` > 0.90 AND
   375	   `/analysis/holm_s1_pass` AND `/analysis/holm_s2_pass` AND
   376	   `/analysis/gold_replication_identical`.
   377	4. else **INCONCLUSIVE** (re-opens FK-NLB-2 with data).
