    16	primary and S2 numerators are therefore scored over the 7 shape-recoverable
    17	IN-SCOPE families only (n_scored = 527), as per-family BUCKET SUMS over the
    18	score_nl by_family enrichment (ASM-0480). The run still EXECUTES all 600
    19	covered phrasings; the 2 dropped families (unique-maker 43, made-lookup 30)
    20	are reported DESCRIPTIVELY in /analysis/shape_ambiguous_stratum, never
    21	gated, carved out of the envelope. Full-run descriptives (parse_ok_rate over
    22	870, label strata, stage breakdown, dev, probe, cost) stay full-run.
    23	
    24	SKEPTIC-ROUND-2 HARDENING (design doc 14.8, ASM-0621; all fail-closed):
    25	  G0 one-row-per-arm: duplicate/retry rows for the same arm are NEVER
    26	     resolved by log order. A re-run row must carry a top-level
    27	     `supersedes: [<sha256 of the replaced body's sorted-keys JSON>]`;
    28	     any arm with >1 non-superseded row, or any dangling supersede target,
    29	     invalidates the instrument in BOTH log orders.
    30	  G7 harness-pin enforcement: the pins_observed emitted by the instrument
    31	     (engine, nlb_instrument/nlb_frontend/nlb_map, corpus digests, phrasing
    32	     corpus files, lint receipt) must equal the frozen manifest constants
    33	     below on EVERY arm body; a missing pin block or any drift fails closed.
    34	     The pinned lint-receipt sha transitively enforces the receipt content,
    35	     incl. waived_forced_substring == [] for l3a (ASM-0423).
    36	  G5 existence: a missing/empty deranged arm or absent n_covered_exact is a
    37	     BROKEN instrument, never "perfect collapse".
    38	  G1 full counts integrity: run-level covered partition
    39	     (exact+wrong+refused_parse+refused_engine == 600), control partition
    40	     (answered+acceptable+other == 270; refused_any == acceptable+other;
    41	     acceptable == strict+parse on the mapper arm, which never emits
    42	     ABSTAIN), family-key set equality (no unexpected families), per-family
    43	     bucket partition + exact == ok, bucket sums == run-level twins,
    44	     zero covered buckets on control families, all buckets non-negative
    45	     integers, in-scope n_scored == 527.
    46	
    47	Endpoints (design doc section 6 + 14.2, verdict rules in the record):
    48	  primary   retained covered exactness == absolute covered-exact rate over
    49	            the 527 shape-recoverable covered queries (gold ceiling MEASURED
    50	            600/600), one-sided Wilson 95% LB (z=1.645) vs floor 0.90; UB
    51	            feeds the FAIL rule.
    52	  S1/S2     ONE Holm family (m=2, family alpha 0.05): control acceptable
    53	            refusal (> 0.95 over 270, run-level totals unchanged) and covered
    54	            wrong-answer over the 527 in-scope slice (UB < 0.02). Step-down:
    55	            the smaller one-sided score-test p is tested at alpha/2 (Wilson
    56	            bound at z=1.96), the other at alpha (z=1.645) only if the first
    57	            passed. The S2 kill leg (covered_wrong_answer_wilson_lb, z=1.645)
    58	            is exported unadjusted.
    59	  descriptive: shape-ambiguous stratum, stage breakdown, label-verbatim vs
    60	            paraphrase strata, dev abstention, synonym probe (never gated),
    61	            front-end cost, audit-r1 reference.
    62	
    63	Instrument gates G0-G7 (any failure => instrument_valid False):
    64	  G0 one-row-per-arm (fail-closed supersede semantics above);
    65	  G1 arm presence + counts + per-family strata match the frozen manifest
    66	     (600 covered / 270 control / 60 dev) PLUS the 14.7 + 14.8 counts-
    67	     integrity extensions above;
    68	  G2 gold-replication parent-perfect (600/600 covered exact, 300/300
    69	     strict-code control, zero wrong/answered);
    70	  G3 phrasing-corpus lint receipt present + green + pinned corpus sha match;
    71	  G4 dev abstention <= 0.20 (12/60);
    72	  G5 deranged-lexicon arm EXISTS with integer counts over the full covered
    73	     set and retained exactness < 0.10;
    74	  G6 mapper-parse doubled pass byte-identical;
    75	  G7 observed harness pins equal the frozen manifest on every arm.
    76	
    77	Fixtures (--selftest) sit ON the pre-computed decision boundaries of the
    78	design doc section 14.2 power table (n=527; independently recomputed
    79	2026-07-10): 486/527 -> LB 0.9008 > 0.90 vs 485 -> 0.8987; UB(462) 0.8983
    80	<= 0.90 fires FAIL vs 463 -> 0.9001; S1 Holm-worst 264/270 -> LB(z=1.96)
    81	0.9524 > 0.95 vs 263 -> 0.9475; S2 4/527 -> UB(z=1.96) 0.0194 < 0.02 vs
    82	5 -> 0.0220; S2 kill 16/527 -> LB(z=1.645) 0.0203 >= 0.02 vs 15 -> 0.0187.
    83	The gated numerators are BUCKET SUMS over the 7 in-scope families, so the
    84	boundary fixtures place the varied counts in in-scope families; an isolation
    85	fixture proves a wrong answer in a shape-ambiguous family moves no gate;
    86	round-2 fixtures prove duplicate arms invalidate in both log orders, an
    87	explicit supersede is honoured, an empty deranged arm fails G5, harness-pin
    88	drift fails G7, and every counts-integrity breach fails G1.
    89	"""
    90	import hashlib
    91	import json
    92	import sys
    93	
    94	EXPERIMENT = "l3a-parse"
    95	Z_PRIMARY = 1.645   # one-sided 95%, matches kot_common.wilson_lower_bound
    96	Z_HOLM_FIRST = 1.96  # alpha/2 leg of the m=2 Holm step-down
    97	FLOOR = 0.90
    98	S1_GATE = 0.95
    99	S2_GATE = 0.02
   100	DERANGED_MAX = 0.10
   101	DEV_MAX_ABSTENTION = 0.20
   102	
   103	PLANNED_COVERED = 600
   104	PLANNED_CONTROL = 270
   105	PLANNED_DEV = 60
   106	# FK-NLB-10 / ASM-0420: the gated slice is the 7 shape-recoverable families
   107	# (n_scored = 527); the 2 shape-ambiguous families are descriptive only.
   108	IN_SCOPE_FAMILIES = ("children-lookup", "count-maker",
   109	                     "instance-false-disjoint", "instance-true",
   110	                     "part-lookup", "unique-father", "unique-mother")
   111	SHAPE_AMBIGUOUS_FAMILIES = ("unique-maker", "made-lookup")
   112	N_SCORED = 527
   113	PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA = {
   114	    "children-lookup": 100, "count-maker": 43, "instance-false-disjoint": 40,
   115	    "instance-true": 50, "made-lookup": 30, "part-lookup": 50,
   116	    "unique-father": 122, "unique-maker": 43, "unique-mother": 122}
   117	PLANNED_CONTROL_STRATA = {
   118	    "conflict": 20, "instance-no-record": 20, "no-record": 60,
   119	    "out-of-scope-rel": 60, "unknown-entity": 40, "unlicensed-count": 30,
   120	    "unlicensed-unique": 40}
   121	EXPECTED_FAMILIES = frozenset(PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA) | \
   122	    frozenset(PLANNED_CONTROL_STRATA)
   123	BUCKET_KEYS = ("exact", "wrong", "refused_parse", "refused_engine")
   124	GOLD_PERFECT = {"n_covered": 600, "n_covered_exact": 600,
   125	                "n_control": 300, "n_control_refused_correct_code": 300,
   126	                "n_covered_answered_wrong": 0, "n_control_answered": 0}
   127	AUDIT_R1_REF = {
   128	    "path": "data/nlb-phrasings-l3a/audit-recoverability-r1.json",
   129	    "sha256": ("57e9d8d12826ae6ba28da4289fcc703109b2fb"
   130	               "9994ef99eb589655874ea6da6d")}
   131	# EVAL corpus pinned 2026-07-10 (EVAL-BUILD-SPEC step 6): sha256 of
   132	# data/nlb-phrasings-l3a/eval.jsonl, checked against the run's observed
   133	# phrasings_file in G3 (and again in G7). None would disable ONLY the
   134	# G3 sha-equality sub-check.
   135	EXPECTED_PHRASINGS_SHA256 = \
   136	    "832828d892260ee53aff51d648998e3656a2d5dc16b26c55713b638964858d8a"
   137	
   138	# ---- G7 frozen harness manifest (design doc 14.8, ASM-0621): the analysis
   139	# REFUSES any run whose observed pins drift from the record's harness
   140	# manifest / corpus pins. Values byte-copied from
   141	# registry/experiments/l3a-parse.json (pins + harness_manifest) and the
   142	# committed corpus files at the 2026-07-10 input pin.
   143	CORPUS_RECIPE = (
   144	    "kot-corpus-hash/1: digest = sha256 over the UTF-8 concatenation of one "
   145	    "line per regular file under data/<corpus>/ (recursive; symlinks and "
   146	    "directories excluded), each line '<sha256-of-file-bytes-hex>  "
   147	    "<relpath>\\n' with exactly two spaces, relpath POSIX-style "
   148	    "('/'-separated) relative to data/<corpus>/, lines sorted by the UTF-8 "
   149	    "byte order of relpath; reference implementation "
   150	    "tools/registry/corpus-pin.py"
   151	)
   152	EXPECTED_HARNESS_PINS = {
   153	    "engine":
   154	        "d26408815238cd9f73b50bb2c4b1f659c8a783ff6a5f16e27357eb2071bb3d08",
   155	    "nlb_instrument.py":
   156	        "3d92e1ab7ef71ae577f63f8955f4381bc90a7c257e44102089220b96e25853d2",
   157	    "nlb_frontend.py":
   158	        "590377760ed5067688ddc0dd859c1a1cfa955e640b3a07c0f75e91d3bc908ea0",
   159	    "nlb_map.mjs":
   160	        "6256fc019cd4be8e64708565475976c90237bf25cd46908379c25ee7fa3d7084",
   161	    "corpus_axioms-v0":
   162	        "bfcb2f45969b9fe9beb41bcb435d66c078aab3b01d8e6ec387c1bf36b52da718",
   163	    "corpus_world-v0":
   164	        "dfa5145167b1365681b640f91c766f0a46da28af6941f35a56d00aff35408f9a",
   165	    "corpus_l3a-eval":
   166	        "53eb788b1681960b55436a4566df5d9fabe5efb3c57399e90fcfa2d13afb98e7",
   167	    "corpus_kernel-v0":
   168	        "8209cadabcfc2eaa11631c5c1100c04a48f33673516780b1f36cbf957217c809",
   169	    "corpus_molecules-v0":
   170	        "69f0c8a354ce489d15e9156d611932ba548f80c41e78af4ffe597192067a59c4",
   171	    "corpus_file_eval.jsonl": EXPECTED_PHRASINGS_SHA256,
   172	    "corpus_file_dev.jsonl":
   173	        "3022a6762148808f9083d412231aa6b790d6c7d1d5e44e58dc3c3134a5851230",
   174	    "corpus_file_dev-entities.jsonl":
   175	        "eda2721d17c712253d51d23fc10b27f9191322273043ca6667597d6e59518cd9",
   176	    "corpus_file_probe.jsonl":
   177	        "11c4bfee8587346bbec8bba0600fc26195b7f37d006f173328218f86c5a8aac2",
   178	    "corpus_file_manifest.json":
   179	        "63002038da1667985fa507a3ecc5d62d95f14b2f47a7458d8db22a3d2445e436",
   180	    # lint receipt: green, findings [], waived_forced_substring [] — the sha
   181	    # pin transitively enforces the EMPTY l3a waived list (ASM-0423).
   182	    "phrasings_lint":
   183	        "9716a8551349b0fd7d99d01e012fbce93d9f134ec80de8b55449dc2b48c56aed",
   184	    "phrasings_file": EXPECTED_PHRASINGS_SHA256,
   185	}
   186	
   187	ARMS = ("mapper-parse", "gold-replication", "deranged-lexicon",
   188	        "abstain-all", "answer-all")
   189	
   190	
   191	def wilson(p, n, z, upper=False):
   192	    if n <= 0:
   193	        return 1.0 if upper else 0.0
   194	    z2 = z * z
   195	    centre = p + z2 / (2 * n)
   196	    spread = z * ((p * (1 - p) / n + z2 / (4 * n * n)) ** 0.5)
   197	    return (centre + spread if upper else centre - spread) / (1 + z2 / n)
   198	
   199	
   200	def score_z(p_hat, p0, n, direction):
   201	    """One-sided score-test statistic used ONLY to order the two Holm
   202	    hypotheses (larger z == smaller p). direction 'gt': H1 p > p0;
   203	    'lt': H1 p < p0."""
   204	    se = (p0 * (1 - p0) / n) ** 0.5 if n > 0 else 1.0
   205	    z = (p_hat - p0) / se if se > 0 else 0.0
   206	    return z if direction == "gt" else -z
   207	
   208	
   209	def _count(v):
   210	    """A well-formed counter: non-negative int (bool excluded)."""
   211	    return isinstance(v, int) and not isinstance(v, bool) and v >= 0
   212	
   213	
   214	def _body_sha(r):
   215	    """Identity of one run-record body for the G0 supersede mechanism:
   216	    sha256 over its sorted-keys JSON bytes."""
   217	    return hashlib.sha256(
   218	        json.dumps(r, sort_keys=True).encode("utf-8")).hexdigest()
   219	
   220	
   221	def _one_row_per_arm(records):
   222	    """G0 (fail-closed; design doc 14.8, ASM-0621): duplicate/retry rows are
   223	    never resolved by log order. Returns (by_arm, ok, detail)."""
   224	    eligible = [r for r in records
   225	                if r.get("experiment") in (None, EXPERIMENT)]
   226	    shas = [_body_sha(r) for r in eligible]
   227	    sha_set = set(shas)
   228	    superseded, dangling = set(), []
   229	    for r in eligible:
   230	        for s in (r.get("supersedes") or []):
   231	            if s not in sha_set:
   232	                dangling.append(s)
   233	            superseded.add(s)
   234	    by_arm, dup = {}, []
   235	    for r, s in zip(eligible, shas):
   236	        if s in superseded:
   237	            continue
   238	        arm = r.get("config", {}).get("arm") or r.get("arm")
   239	        if arm in by_arm:
   240	            dup.append(arm)
   241	        by_arm[arm] = r
   242	    ok = not dup and not dangling
   243	    detail = {"duplicate_arms": sorted(set(dup)),
   244	              "dangling_supersedes": sorted(set(dangling))}
   245	    return by_arm, ok, detail
   246	
   247	
   248	def _pins_ok(body):
   249	    """G7: observed harness pins on one arm body equal the frozen manifest
   250	    (fail-closed on a missing pins block or any missing/drifted key)."""
   251	    po = body.get("pins_observed")
   252	    if not isinstance(po, dict) or po.get("_recipe") != CORPUS_RECIPE:
   253	        return False
   254	    for key, want in EXPECTED_HARNESS_PINS.items():
   255	        v = po.get(key)
   256	        if not isinstance(v, dict) or v.get("observed") != want:
   257	            return False
   258	    return True
   259	
   260	
   261	def analyze(records):
   262	    out = {"gates": {"instrument_valid": False}, "analysis": {}}
   263	    by_arm, g0, g0_detail = _one_row_per_arm(records)
   264	    out["gates"]["g0_one_row_per_arm"] = bool(g0)
   265	    if not g0:
   266	        out["gates"]["g0_detail"] = g0_detail
   267	        return out
   268	    mp = by_arm.get("mapper-parse")
   269	    gold = by_arm.get("gold-replication")
   270	    der = by_arm.get("deranged-lexicon")
   271	    if mp is None:
   272	        return out
   273	    m = mp["metrics"]
   274	    nc, ng = m.get("n_covered", 0), m.get("n_control", 0)
   275	    n_exact = m.get("n_covered_exact", 0)
   276	    n_wrong = m.get("n_covered_answered_wrong", 0)
   277	    n_rparse = m.get("n_covered_refused_parse", 0)
   278	    n_rengine = m.get("n_covered_refused_engine", 0)
   279	    n_ctl_acc = m.get("n_control_refused_acceptable", 0)
   280	    n_ctl_ans = m.get("n_control_answered", 0)
   281	    n_ctl_other = m.get("n_control_refused_other", 0)
   282	    n_ctl_any = m.get("n_control_refused_any", 0)
   283	    n_ctl_strict = m.get("n_control_refused_strict_engine_code", 0)
   284	    n_ctl_parse = m.get("n_control_refused_parse", 0)
   285	    dev_n = m.get("dev_n", 0)
   286	    dev_ref = m.get("dev_parse_refused", 0)
   287	    fam = m.get("by_family", {})
   288	
   289	    def buck(k, key):
   290	        return fam.get(k, {}).get(key, 0)
   291	
   292	    # ---- G1 counts integrity (14.7 + 14.8 extensions; any failure =>
   293	    # instrument-invalid). Well-formedness first, so nothing below can
   294	    # arithmetic over a malformed bucket.
   295	    fam_keys_ok = isinstance(fam, dict) and set(fam) == EXPECTED_FAMILIES
   296	    buckets_wellformed = fam_keys_ok and all(
   297	        isinstance(fam[k], dict) and
   298	        all(_count(fam[k].get(b)) for b in ("n", "ok") + BUCKET_KEYS)
   299	        for k in EXPECTED_FAMILIES)
   300	    if buckets_wellformed:
   301	        strata_ok = all(fam[k]["n"] == v for k, v in
   302	                        list(PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA.items()) +
   303	                        list(PLANNED_CONTROL_STRATA.items()))
   304	        # (i) in-scope n_scored == 527 (gated numerators are bucket sums over
   305	        # the 7 in-scope families only — FK-NLB-10, ASM-0420; the two dropped
   306	        # families' outcomes never enter a gate)
   307	        n_scored = sum(buck(k, "n") for k in IN_SCOPE_FAMILIES)
   308	        exact_in = sum(buck(k, "exact") for k in IN_SCOPE_FAMILIES)
   309	        wrong_in = sum(buck(k, "wrong") for k in IN_SCOPE_FAMILIES)
   310	        scored_ok = (n_scored == N_SCORED)
   311	        # (ii) per covered family the bucket partition holds and exact == ok
   312	        partition_ok = all(
   313	            sum(buck(k, b) for b in BUCKET_KEYS) == buck(k, "n") and
   314	            buck(k, "exact") == buck(k, "ok")
   315	            for k in PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA)
   316	        # (iii) covered-family bucket sums equal the run-level twins
   317	        twins_ok = (
   318	            sum(buck(k, "exact") for k in PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA) == n_exact
   319	            and sum(buck(k, "wrong") for k in PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA)
   320	            == n_wrong and
   321	            sum(buck(k, "refused_parse") for k in PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA)
   322	            == n_rparse and
   323	            sum(buck(k, "refused_engine") for k in PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA)
   324	            == n_rengine)
   325	        # (iv) control families hold zero covered buckets; ok <= n
   326	        control_zero_ok = all(
   327	            all(buck(k, b) == 0 for b in BUCKET_KEYS) and
   328	            buck(k, "ok") <= buck(k, "n")
   329	            for k in PLANNED_CONTROL_STRATA)
   330	    else:
   331	        strata_ok = scored_ok = partition_ok = twins_ok = False
   332	        control_zero_ok = False
   333	        n_scored = exact_in = wrong_in = 0
   334	    # (v) run-level covered outcome partition over 600
   335	    run_counts = (n_exact, n_wrong, n_rparse, n_rengine)
   336	    run_partition_ok = (all(_count(x) for x in run_counts) and
   337	                        sum(run_counts) == nc)
   338	    # (vi) run-level control outcome partition over 270 (mapper arm: the
   339	    # acceptable set is strict-engine-code + ERR_PARSE — FK-NLB-6; the
   340	    # ABSTAIN branch exists only on the abstain-all arm, never here)
   341	    ctl_counts = (n_ctl_acc, n_ctl_ans, n_ctl_other, n_ctl_any,
   342	                  n_ctl_strict, n_ctl_parse)
   343	    ctl_partition_ok = (all(_count(x) for x in ctl_counts) and
   344	                        n_ctl_ans + n_ctl_acc + n_ctl_other == ng and
   345	                        n_ctl_any == n_ctl_acc + n_ctl_other and
   346	                        n_ctl_acc == n_ctl_strict + n_ctl_parse)
   347	    g1 = (all(a in by_arm for a in ARMS) and nc == PLANNED_COVERED and
   348	          ng == PLANNED_CONTROL and dev_n == PLANNED_DEV and fam_keys_ok and
   349	          buckets_wellformed and strata_ok and scored_ok and partition_ok and
   350	          twins_ok and control_zero_ok and run_partition_ok and
   351	          ctl_partition_ok)
   352	    gm = gold["metrics"] if gold else {}
   353	    g2 = all(gm.get(k) == v for k, v in GOLD_PERFECT.items())
   354	    lint = (mp.get("pins_observed", {}) or {}).get("phrasings_lint", {})
   355	    g3 = bool(lint.get("green"))
   356	    if EXPECTED_PHRASINGS_SHA256 is not None:
   357	        pf = (mp.get("pins_observed", {}) or {}).get("phrasings_file", {})
   358	        g3 = g3 and pf.get("observed") == EXPECTED_PHRASINGS_SHA256
   359	    g4 = dev_n > 0 and (dev_ref / float(dev_n)) <= DEV_MAX_ABSTENTION
   360	    # G5 (14.8 hardening): the deranged arm must EXIST, cover the full
   361	    # planned covered set, and report an explicit integer exact count —
   362	    # a missing arm or missing metric is a broken instrument, NEVER
   363	    # "perfect collapse".
   364	    dm = der["metrics"] if der else {}
   365	    if der is not None and dm.get("n_covered") == PLANNED_COVERED and \
   366	            _count(dm.get("n_covered")) and _count(dm.get("n_covered_exact")):
   367	        der_rate = dm["n_covered_exact"] / float(dm["n_covered"])
   368	        g5 = der_rate < DERANGED_MAX
   369	    else:
   370	        der_rate = None
   371	        g5 = False
   372	    g6 = m.get("deterministic_repeat_identical") is True
   373	    g7 = all(a in by_arm and _pins_ok(by_arm[a]) for a in ARMS)
   374	    out["gates"].update({"g1_counts": g1, "g2_gold_replication": g2,
   375	                         "g3_phrasing_lints": g3, "g4_dev_abstention": g4,
   376	                         "g5_deranged_collapse": g5, "g6_determinism": g6,
   377	                         "g7_harness_pins": g7})
   378	    out["gates"]["instrument_valid"] = all((g0, g1, g2, g3, g4, g5, g6, g7))
   379	
   380	    # ---- primary (retained == absolute over the 527 in-scope slice;
   381	    # measured gold ceiling 600/600)
   382	    a = out["analysis"]
   383	    cov = exact_in / float(N_SCORED) if N_SCORED else 0.0
   384	    a["n_covered_run"] = nc          # 600 executed (replaces n_covered)
   385	    a["n_covered_scored"] = N_SCORED  # 527 gated (FK-NLB-10)
   386	    a["n_control"], a["n_dev"] = ng, dev_n
   387	    a["retained_covered_exact_rate"] = cov
   388	    a["retained_covered_exact_wilson_lb"] = wilson(cov, N_SCORED, Z_PRIMARY)
   389	    a["retained_covered_exact_wilson_ub"] = wilson(cov, N_SCORED, Z_PRIMARY,
   390	                                                   True)
   391	
   392	    # ---- secondaries (one Holm family, m=2): S1 run-level over 270,
   393	    # S2 over the 527 in-scope slice
   394	    ctl = n_ctl_acc / float(ng) if ng else 0.0
   395	    wrong = wrong_in / float(N_SCORED) if N_SCORED else 1.0
   396	    a["control_refusal_acceptable_rate"] = ctl
   397	    a["control_refusal_acceptable_wilson_lb"] = wilson(ctl, ng, Z_PRIMARY)
   398	    a["control_refusal_strict_engine_code_rate"] = (
   399	        m.get("n_control_refused_strict_engine_code", 0) / float(ng)
   400	        if ng else 0.0)
   401	    a["covered_wrong_answer_rate"] = wrong
   402	    a["covered_wrong_answer_wilson_ub"] = wilson(wrong, N_SCORED, Z_PRIMARY,
   403	                                                 True)
   404	    a["covered_wrong_answer_wilson_lb"] = wilson(wrong, N_SCORED, Z_PRIMARY)
   405	
   406	    def s1_pass_at(z):
   407	        return wilson(ctl, ng, z) > S1_GATE
   408	
   409	    def s2_pass_at(z):
   410	        return wilson(wrong, N_SCORED, z, upper=True) < S2_GATE
   411	
   412	    z_s1 = score_z(ctl, S1_GATE, ng, "gt")
   413	    z_s2 = score_z(wrong, S2_GATE, N_SCORED, "lt")
   414	    if z_s1 >= z_s2:  # S1 has the smaller p -> tested at alpha/2
   415	        s1 = s1_pass_at(Z_HOLM_FIRST)
   416	        s2 = s1 and s2_pass_at(Z_PRIMARY)
   417	    else:
   418	        s2 = s2_pass_at(Z_HOLM_FIRST)
   419	        s1 = s2 and s1_pass_at(Z_PRIMARY)
   420	    a["holm_s1_pass"] = bool(s1)
     1	#!/usr/bin/env python3
     2	"""a5-nl pinned analysis — NL-boundary leg, code vertical (HA5 NL analog of
     3	HL3a clause 2; DRAFT record registry/experiments/a5-nl.json).
     4	
     5	Eligible run records on stdin (one JSON per line, kot-log/1 bodies from
     6	tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_instrument.py); analysis-output JSON on stdout.
     7	Derived statistics live HERE and nowhere else (P2 G-4). Self-contained by
     8	design: no shared helper import, so the pinned sha is the complete analysis
     9	artifact (structural twin of analysis/l3a_parse.py with per-record constants;
    10	a5-nl is NOT re-scoped — FK-NLB-10 is l3a-only — so the gated numerators
    11	stay run-level over the full 855, and the ASM-0480 by_family buckets are
    12	consumed HERE as counts-integrity invariants, not as a scope cut).
    13	
    14	SKEPTIC-ROUND-2 HARDENING (design doc 14.8, ASM-0621; all fail-closed):
    15	  G0 one-row-per-arm: duplicate/retry rows for the same arm are NEVER
    16	     resolved by log order. A re-run row must carry a top-level
    17	     `supersedes: [<sha256 of the replaced body's sorted-keys JSON>]`;
    18	     any arm with >1 non-superseded row, or any dangling supersede target,
    19	     invalidates the instrument in BOTH log orders.
    20	  G7 harness-pin enforcement: the pins_observed emitted by the instrument
    21	     (engine, kot_code desugar layer, nlb_instrument/nlb_frontend/nlb_map,
    22	     corpus digests, phrasing corpus files, lint receipt) must equal the
    23	     frozen manifest constants below on EVERY arm body; a missing pin block
    24	     or any drift fails closed. The pinned lint-receipt sha transitively
    25	     enforces the receipt content, incl. the DISCLOSED 28-item
    26	     waived_forced_substring list (FK-NLB-11 / ASM-0423 — lawful ONLY for
    27	     this record's non-model arms; the pinned nlb_lint blocks green for
    28	     model-arm reuse by default).
    29	  G5 existence: a missing/empty deranged arm or absent n_covered_exact is a
    30	     BROKEN instrument, never "perfect collapse".
    31	  G1 full counts integrity: run-level covered partition
    32	     (exact+wrong+refused_parse+refused_engine == 855), control partition
    33	     (answered+acceptable+other == 106; refused_any == acceptable+other;
    34	     acceptable == strict+parse on the mapper arm, which never emits
    35	     ABSTAIN), family-key set equality (no unexpected families), per-family
    36	     bucket partition + exact == ok, bucket sums == run-level twins,
    37	     zero covered buckets on control families, all buckets non-negative
    38	     integers.
    39	
    40	Endpoints (design doc section 6, verdict rules in the record):
    41	  primary   retained covered exactness == absolute covered-exact rate
    42	            (gold ceiling MEASURED 855/855), one-sided Wilson 95% LB
    43	            (z=1.645) vs floor 0.90; UB feeds the FAIL rule.
    44	  S1/S2     ONE Holm family (m=2, family alpha 0.05): control acceptable
    45	            refusal (> 0.90 over 106 — FK-NLB-7 gate level, decidability at
    46	            the small control n) and covered wrong-answer (UB < 0.02 over
    47	            855). Step-down: the smaller one-sided score-test p is tested at
    48	            alpha/2 (Wilson bound at z=1.96), the other at alpha (z=1.645)
    49	            only if the first passed. The S2 kill leg
    50	            (covered_wrong_answer_wilson_lb, z=1.645) is exported unadjusted.
    51	  descriptive: stage breakdown, label-verbatim vs paraphrase strata, dev
    52	            abstention, synonym probe (never gated), front-end cost.
    53	
    54	Instrument gates G0-G7 (any failure => instrument_valid False):
    55	  G0 one-row-per-arm (fail-closed supersede semantics above);
    56	  G1 arm presence + counts + per-family strata match the frozen manifest
    57	     (855 covered / 106 control / 60 dev) PLUS the 14.8 counts-integrity
    58	     extensions above;
    59	  G2 gold-replication parent-perfect (855/855 covered exact, 122/122
    60	     strict-code control, zero wrong/answered);
    61	  G3 phrasing-corpus lint receipt present + green + pinned corpus sha match;
    62	  G4 dev abstention <= 0.20 (12/60);
    63	  G5 deranged-lexicon arm EXISTS with integer counts over the full covered
    64	     set and retained exactness < 0.10;
    65	  G6 mapper-parse doubled pass byte-identical;
    66	  G7 observed harness pins equal the frozen manifest on every arm.
    67	
    68	Fixtures (--selftest) sit ON the pre-computed decision boundaries
    69	(independently recomputed 2026-07-10; two informative values in the DRAFT
    70	section 7 table were corrected at freeze-candidate time): 784/855 ->
    71	LB 0.9001 > 0.90 vs 783 -> 0.8988; UB(755) 0.8999 <= 0.90 fires FAIL vs
    72	756 -> 0.9010; S1 Holm-worst 102/106 -> LB(z=1.96) 0.9070 > 0.90 vs
    73	101 -> 0.8943; S2 9/855 -> UB(z=1.96) 0.0199 < 0.02 vs 10 -> 0.0214; S2 kill
    74	24/855 -> LB(z=1.645) 0.0202 >= 0.02 vs 23 -> 0.0192. The varied counts are
    75	placed in the contained-in family so the by_family twins integrity holds by
    76	construction; round-2 fixtures prove duplicate arms invalidate in both log
    77	orders, an explicit supersede is honoured, an empty deranged arm fails G5,
    78	harness-pin drift fails G7, and every counts-integrity breach fails G1
    79	(including the reproduced n_covered_exact=855 AND n_covered_refused_parse=855
    80	conflict).
    81	"""
    82	import hashlib
    83	import json
    84	import sys
    85	
    86	EXPERIMENT = "a5-nl"
    87	Z_PRIMARY = 1.645   # one-sided 95%, matches kot_common.wilson_lower_bound
    88	Z_HOLM_FIRST = 1.96  # alpha/2 leg of the m=2 Holm step-down
    89	FLOOR = 0.90
    90	S1_GATE = 0.90  # FK-NLB-7: 0.95 is undecidable at n=106 under Holm-worst
    91	S2_GATE = 0.02
    92	DERANGED_MAX = 0.10
    93	DEV_MAX_ABSTENTION = 0.20
    94	
    95	PLANNED_COVERED = 855
    96	PLANNED_CONTROL = 106
    97	PLANNED_DEV = 60
    98	PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA = {
    99	    "callees-of": 73, "callers-of": 74, "contained-in": 201, "contains": 41,
   100	    "imported-by": 2, "imports-of": 9, "instance-false-disjoint": 38,
   101	    "instance-true": 216, "where-defined": 201}
   102	PLANNED_CONTROL_STRATA = {
   103	    "conflict": 5, "no-record-callees": 15, "no-record-callers": 15,
   104	    "no-record-contains": 10, "no-record-imported-by": 10,
   105	    "no-record-imports": 6, "out-of-scope-concept": 6, "unknown-entity": 24,
   106	    "unlicensed-unique": 15}
   107	EXPECTED_FAMILIES = frozenset(PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA) | \
   108	    frozenset(PLANNED_CONTROL_STRATA)
   109	BUCKET_KEYS = ("exact", "wrong", "refused_parse", "refused_engine")
   110	GOLD_PERFECT = {"n_covered": 855, "n_covered_exact": 855,
   111	                "n_control": 122, "n_control_refused_correct_code": 122,
   112	                "n_covered_answered_wrong": 0, "n_control_answered": 0}
   113	# EVAL corpus pinned 2026-07-10 (EVAL-BUILD-SPEC step 6): sha256 of
   114	# data/nlb-phrasings-a5/eval.jsonl, checked against the run's observed
   115	# phrasings_file in G3 (and again in G7). None would disable ONLY the
   116	# G3 sha-equality sub-check.
   117	EXPECTED_PHRASINGS_SHA256 = \
   118	    "746b202d27239cc1b49aa611696387080313a7116c48a8ce5cad2f963d3489c6"
   119	
   120	# ---- G7 frozen harness manifest (design doc 14.8, ASM-0621): the analysis
   121	# REFUSES any run whose observed pins drift from the record's harness
   122	# manifest / corpus pins. Values byte-copied from
   123	# registry/experiments/a5-nl.json (pins + harness_manifest) and the
   124	# committed corpus files at the 2026-07-10 input pin.
   125	CORPUS_RECIPE = (
   126	    "kot-corpus-hash/1: digest = sha256 over the UTF-8 concatenation of one "
   127	    "line per regular file under data/<corpus>/ (recursive; symlinks and "
   128	    "directories excluded), each line '<sha256-of-file-bytes-hex>  "
   129	    "<relpath>\\n' with exactly two spaces, relpath POSIX-style "
   130	    "('/'-separated) relative to data/<corpus>/, lines sorted by the UTF-8 "
   131	    "byte order of relpath; reference implementation "
   132	    "tools/registry/corpus-pin.py"
   133	)
   134	EXPECTED_HARNESS_PINS = {
   135	    "engine":
   136	        "d26408815238cd9f73b50bb2c4b1f659c8a783ff6a5f16e27357eb2071bb3d08",
   137	    "code_layer":
   138	        "9fbe2a50dcd80e100a8a32ffb5d455e9ce993424fbf0bd293b8143aef96bb99a",
   139	    "nlb_instrument.py":
   140	        "3d92e1ab7ef71ae577f63f8955f4381bc90a7c257e44102089220b96e25853d2",
   141	    "nlb_frontend.py":
   142	        "590377760ed5067688ddc0dd859c1a1cfa955e640b3a07c0f75e91d3bc908ea0",
   143	    "nlb_map.mjs":
   144	        "6256fc019cd4be8e64708565475976c90237bf25cd46908379c25ee7fa3d7084",
   145	    "corpus_code-axioms-v0":
   146	        "dc930b4fdeb95994828d8b7b0a184e5d96714a3b7f51269f7d46cba5b14e39e3",
   147	    "corpus_code-world-v0":
   148	        "b8a8a50a3111425685cb2041061f72e4d0d89da17cb073fdffe11b338f26aef9",
   149	    "corpus_a5-eval":
   150	        "3676d689277660f80f7cfac9823ecb7b9b40a73777ad538623405c5c1e903843",
   151	    "corpus_kernel-v0":
   152	        "8209cadabcfc2eaa11631c5c1100c04a48f33673516780b1f36cbf957217c809",
   153	    "corpus_molecules-v0":
   154	        "69f0c8a354ce489d15e9156d611932ba548f80c41e78af4ffe597192067a59c4",
   155	    "corpus_code-v0":
   156	        "01009b1fc0c6e34b0c49b294e0cb159695831070fbe6808957694f46d03abd83",
   157	    "corpus_code-corpus-v0":
   158	        "1063ad50ff694d8548296f42c17f296027768a87dba98f534e9f2ea7f7c5fea3",
   159	    "corpus_file_eval.jsonl": EXPECTED_PHRASINGS_SHA256,
   160	    "corpus_file_dev.jsonl":
   161	        "09bc68f012245eb96ca745ffeeef45a9a062bb08a2b79ffebd24ceba11fba1a3",
   162	    "corpus_file_dev-entities.jsonl":
   163	        "f95517ff2b47f299ecbffce9f7ef6b029b7fb6ddb213a719735e539a738737d1",
   164	    "corpus_file_probe.jsonl":
   165	        "8ca0458c7f45e79f7a7886089b1bb6446cb386453c901e7886e4a13d62acbdf1",
   166	    "corpus_file_manifest.json":
   167	        "38120781d93521e60898572f0bbe1f93e26f9afbf89e0120ea1231c5f1a45107",
   168	    # lint receipt: green, findings [], waived_forced_substring = the 28
   169	    # DISCLOSED forced-substring qids (FK-NLB-11 / ASM-0423) — the sha pin
   170	    # transitively enforces exactly that list, no more, no less.
   171	    "phrasings_lint":
   172	        "cc8a286e4165cfa949b8c679990b65cc6ff5f8723aeaf581dd9ef525be4c8c83",
   173	    "phrasings_file": EXPECTED_PHRASINGS_SHA256,
   174	}
   175	
   176	ARMS = ("mapper-parse", "gold-replication", "deranged-lexicon",
   177	        "abstain-all", "answer-all")
   178	
   179	
   180	def wilson(p, n, z, upper=False):
   181	    if n <= 0:
   182	        return 1.0 if upper else 0.0
   183	    z2 = z * z
   184	    centre = p + z2 / (2 * n)
   185	    spread = z * ((p * (1 - p) / n + z2 / (4 * n * n)) ** 0.5)
   186	    return (centre + spread if upper else centre - spread) / (1 + z2 / n)
   187	
   188	
   189	def score_z(p_hat, p0, n, direction):
   190	    """One-sided score-test statistic used ONLY to order the two Holm
   191	    hypotheses (larger z == smaller p). direction 'gt': H1 p > p0;
   192	    'lt': H1 p < p0."""
   193	    se = (p0 * (1 - p0) / n) ** 0.5 if n > 0 else 1.0
   194	    z = (p_hat - p0) / se if se > 0 else 0.0
   195	    return z if direction == "gt" else -z
   196	
   197	
   198	def _count(v):
   199	    """A well-formed counter: non-negative int (bool excluded)."""
   200	    return isinstance(v, int) and not isinstance(v, bool) and v >= 0
   201	
   202	
   203	def _body_sha(r):
   204	    """Identity of one run-record body for the G0 supersede mechanism:
   205	    sha256 over its sorted-keys JSON bytes."""
   206	    return hashlib.sha256(
   207	        json.dumps(r, sort_keys=True).encode("utf-8")).hexdigest()
   208	
   209	
   210	def _one_row_per_arm(records):
   211	    """G0 (fail-closed; design doc 14.8, ASM-0621): duplicate/retry rows are
   212	    never resolved by log order. Returns (by_arm, ok, detail)."""
   213	    eligible = [r for r in records
   214	                if r.get("experiment") in (None, EXPERIMENT)]
   215	    shas = [_body_sha(r) for r in eligible]
   216	    sha_set = set(shas)
   217	    superseded, dangling = set(), []
   218	    for r in eligible:
   219	        for s in (r.get("supersedes") or []):
   220	            if s not in sha_set:
   221	                dangling.append(s)
   222	            superseded.add(s)
   223	    by_arm, dup = {}, []
   224	    for r, s in zip(eligible, shas):
   225	        if s in superseded:
   226	            continue
   227	        arm = r.get("config", {}).get("arm") or r.get("arm")
   228	        if arm in by_arm:
   229	            dup.append(arm)
   230	        by_arm[arm] = r
   231	    ok = not dup and not dangling
   232	    detail = {"duplicate_arms": sorted(set(dup)),
   233	              "dangling_supersedes": sorted(set(dangling))}
   234	    return by_arm, ok, detail
   235	
   236	
   237	def _pins_ok(body):
   238	    """G7: observed harness pins on one arm body equal the frozen manifest
   239	    (fail-closed on a missing pins block or any missing/drifted key)."""
   240	    po = body.get("pins_observed")
   241	    if not isinstance(po, dict) or po.get("_recipe") != CORPUS_RECIPE:
   242	        return False
   243	    for key, want in EXPECTED_HARNESS_PINS.items():
   244	        v = po.get(key)
   245	        if not isinstance(v, dict) or v.get("observed") != want:
   246	            return False
   247	    return True
   248	
   249	
   250	def analyze(records):
   251	    out = {"gates": {"instrument_valid": False}, "analysis": {}}
   252	    by_arm, g0, g0_detail = _one_row_per_arm(records)
   253	    out["gates"]["g0_one_row_per_arm"] = bool(g0)
   254	    if not g0:
   255	        out["gates"]["g0_detail"] = g0_detail
   256	        return out
   257	    mp = by_arm.get("mapper-parse")
   258	    gold = by_arm.get("gold-replication")
   259	    der = by_arm.get("deranged-lexicon")
   260	    if mp is None:
   261	        return out
   262	    m = mp["metrics"]
   263	    nc, ng = m.get("n_covered", 0), m.get("n_control", 0)
   264	    n_exact = m.get("n_covered_exact", 0)
   265	    n_wrong = m.get("n_covered_answered_wrong", 0)
   266	    n_rparse = m.get("n_covered_refused_parse", 0)
   267	    n_rengine = m.get("n_covered_refused_engine", 0)
   268	    n_ctl_acc = m.get("n_control_refused_acceptable", 0)
   269	    n_ctl_ans = m.get("n_control_answered", 0)
   270	    n_ctl_other = m.get("n_control_refused_other", 0)
   271	    n_ctl_any = m.get("n_control_refused_any", 0)
   272	    n_ctl_strict = m.get("n_control_refused_strict_engine_code", 0)
   273	    n_ctl_parse = m.get("n_control_refused_parse", 0)
   274	    dev_n = m.get("dev_n", 0)
   275	    dev_ref = m.get("dev_parse_refused", 0)
   276	    fam = m.get("by_family", {})
   277	
   278	    def buck(k, key):
   279	        return fam.get(k, {}).get(key, 0)
   280	
   281	    # ---- G1 counts integrity (14.8 extensions; any failure =>
   282	    # instrument-invalid). Well-formedness first, so nothing below can
   283	    # arithmetic over a malformed bucket. a5-nl is NOT re-scoped: the gated
   284	    # numerators are the RUN-LEVEL totals; the by_family buckets are
   285	    # consumed as integrity invariants only.
   286	    fam_keys_ok = isinstance(fam, dict) and set(fam) == EXPECTED_FAMILIES
   287	    buckets_wellformed = fam_keys_ok and all(
   288	        isinstance(fam[k], dict) and
   289	        all(_count(fam[k].get(b)) for b in ("n", "ok") + BUCKET_KEYS)
   290	        for k in EXPECTED_FAMILIES)
   291	    if buckets_wellformed:
   292	        strata_ok = all(fam[k]["n"] == v for k, v in
   293	                        list(PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA.items()) +
   294	                        list(PLANNED_CONTROL_STRATA.items()))
   295	        # (i) per covered family the bucket partition holds and exact == ok
   296	        partition_ok = all(
   297	            sum(buck(k, b) for b in BUCKET_KEYS) == buck(k, "n") and
   298	            buck(k, "exact") == buck(k, "ok")
   299	            for k in PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA)
   300	        # (ii) covered-family bucket sums equal the run-level twins
   301	        twins_ok = (
   302	            sum(buck(k, "exact") for k in PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA) == n_exact
   303	            and sum(buck(k, "wrong") for k in PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA)
   304	            == n_wrong and
   305	            sum(buck(k, "refused_parse") for k in PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA)
   306	            == n_rparse and
   307	            sum(buck(k, "refused_engine") for k in PLANNED_COVERED_STRATA)
   308	            == n_rengine)
   309	        # (iii) control families hold zero covered buckets; ok <= n
   310	        control_zero_ok = all(
   311	            all(buck(k, b) == 0 for b in BUCKET_KEYS) and
   312	            buck(k, "ok") <= buck(k, "n")
   313	            for k in PLANNED_CONTROL_STRATA)
   314	    else:
   315	        strata_ok = partition_ok = twins_ok = control_zero_ok = False
   316	    # (iv) run-level covered outcome partition over 855 (the reproduced
   317	    # finding-6 conflict — e.g. exact=855 AND refused_parse=855 — dies here)
   318	    run_counts = (n_exact, n_wrong, n_rparse, n_rengine)
   319	    run_partition_ok = (all(_count(x) for x in run_counts) and
   320	                        sum(run_counts) == nc)
   321	    # (v) run-level control outcome partition over 106 (mapper arm: the
   322	    # acceptable set is strict-engine-code + ERR_PARSE — FK-NLB-6; the
   323	    # ABSTAIN branch exists only on the abstain-all arm, never here)
   324	    ctl_counts = (n_ctl_acc, n_ctl_ans, n_ctl_other, n_ctl_any,
   325	                  n_ctl_strict, n_ctl_parse)
   326	    ctl_partition_ok = (all(_count(x) for x in ctl_counts) and
   327	                        n_ctl_ans + n_ctl_acc + n_ctl_other == ng and
   328	                        n_ctl_any == n_ctl_acc + n_ctl_other and
   329	                        n_ctl_acc == n_ctl_strict + n_ctl_parse)
   330	    g1 = (all(a in by_arm for a in ARMS) and nc == PLANNED_COVERED and
   331	          ng == PLANNED_CONTROL and dev_n == PLANNED_DEV and fam_keys_ok and
   332	          buckets_wellformed and strata_ok and partition_ok and twins_ok and
   333	          control_zero_ok and run_partition_ok and ctl_partition_ok)
   334	    gm = gold["metrics"] if gold else {}
   335	    g2 = all(gm.get(k) == v for k, v in GOLD_PERFECT.items())
   336	    lint = (mp.get("pins_observed", {}) or {}).get("phrasings_lint", {})
   337	    g3 = bool(lint.get("green"))
   338	    if EXPECTED_PHRASINGS_SHA256 is not None:
   339	        pf = (mp.get("pins_observed", {}) or {}).get("phrasings_file", {})
   340	        g3 = g3 and pf.get("observed") == EXPECTED_PHRASINGS_SHA256
   341	    g4 = dev_n > 0 and (dev_ref / float(dev_n)) <= DEV_MAX_ABSTENTION
   342	    # G5 (14.8 hardening): the deranged arm must EXIST, cover the full
   343	    # planned covered set, and report an explicit integer exact count —
   344	    # a missing arm or missing metric is a broken instrument, NEVER
   345	    # "perfect collapse".
   346	    dm = der["metrics"] if der else {}
   347	    if der is not None and dm.get("n_covered") == PLANNED_COVERED and \
   348	            _count(dm.get("n_covered")) and _count(dm.get("n_covered_exact")):
   349	        der_rate = dm["n_covered_exact"] / float(dm["n_covered"])
   350	        g5 = der_rate < DERANGED_MAX
   351	    else:
   352	        der_rate = None
   353	        g5 = False
