   161	      "metric": "/analysis/retained_covered_exact_wilson_lb",
   162	      "test": "mapper-parse covered-exact rate over the 855 frozen covered queries (one blind NL phrasing each), one-sided Wilson 95% LB (z=1.645, kot_common formula) vs floor 0.90. Retained-fraction form is identical to absolute rate because the gold ceiling is MEASURED at 855/855 (registry/verdicts/a5.json) — non-inferiority margin 0.10 vs measured ceiling 1.0; F2 degenerate-denominator lesson discharged by construction. Floor = ceiling minus the pre-declared 10% maximum NL-boundary loss (ASM-0141, the HA5 analog of HL3a clause 2's 'pre-declared fraction'). Planning value 0.95 (LB 0.9363; corrected from the draft's 0.9351 at freeze-candidate recomputation).",
