   173	      "test": "Holm family member 1 of 2 (family alpha 0.05, one-sided): included-control acceptable-refusal rate (expected engine code OR ERR_PARSE; FK-NLB-6) vs gate 0.90 over n=106. GATE LEVEL 0.90 NOT 0.95 (FK-NLB-7): at n=106 a 0.95 gate is undecidable under the Holm-worst-case bound (only a perfect 106/106 passes — fails the P8 section-1.6 lint); 0.90 passes from 102/106. Planning value 0.99 (Holm-worst z=1.96 LB 0.9476; corrected from the draft's 0.9640 at freeze-candidate recomputation). Strict engine-code rate and refused-any reported descriptively.",
