   184	      "test": "Holm family member 2 of 2: covered mis-parse->wrong-answer rate one-sided Wilson UB vs gate 0.02 over n=855. Planning value 4/855 (UB 0.0120 at z=1.96; corrected from the draft's 0.0132 at freeze-candidate recomputation). Independent kill leg: unadjusted Wilson LB >= 0.02 is a FAIL rule (fires from 24/855; the draft's 25 was an off-by-one, corrected). WILSON_GATE DECLARATION NOTE (design doc 14.8 item 7): the gate block is declared in complement form (expected_rate 0.995, threshold 0.98) because the RT-4 constraint-9 checker powers LB-exceeds-threshold gates only; by the Wilson complement identity LB(1-p,n,z) == 1-UB(p,n,z) this is the IDENTICAL gate — the tested quantity remains the wrong-answer rate UB < 0.02 with unchanged boundaries.",
