113:{"id": "ASM-0422", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB l3a audit r1 protocol (no judge re-roll): audit-recoverability-r1.json is produced by (i) mechanically re-scoring the COMMITTED judge transcript (sha256 7f3f2291a7e46fb554e7477fc92ff3611d4a0131e117aa5c027960563f36fb1a) restricted to the in-scope covered sampled items, and (ii) topping the covered-only sample to 60 via a FRESH judge identity given ONLY new in-scope items (same pinned prompt-audit.md, same deterministic sample rule over the 7 in-scope families, already-judged qids skipped). No item is ever judged twice; the original audit artifact stays committed as the driving evidence and is never overwritten.", "backing_ref": "tools/experiments/nlb/EVAL-BUILD-SPEC.md step 5 (no-re-roll rule); registry/assessments/l3a-parse-recoverability.json; audit sha256 d6365bd95e7d61a1cce7585bb446aa8f905b2b8eec08d0756a446e2e70a09bf5", "rationale": "The spec's no-re-roll rule exists to stop judge-shopping; re-scoring the same committed transcript under the registered split gate and extending the sample with new items to a fresh judge preserves that guarantee while making the gate decidable on the re-scoped population (27 in-scope covered items are already judged, 33 are owed). Revisit condition: none for this pair; a successor audit protocol supersedes it with its own ASM.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
116:{"id": "ASM-0425", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Sizing/expectation note only: the l3a-parse primary planning value 0.95 is implausible - the audit sample measured natural-synonym phrasing on 9/27 = 0.333 of in-scope covered sampled items (count-maker 4/4, part-lookup 4/4, instance-true 1/4), and against the single-label mapper lexicon (no synonym table) those items are expected to abstain, putting the covered-exact rate plausibly in or below the 463-485/527 INCONCLUSIVE band (extrapolated from a 27-item audit sample to the 527-item scored set and from judge label-use to mapper parse behaviour - neither measured end-to-end). Used ONLY to set maintainer expectations that an INCONCLUSIVE/FAIL landing is live; never a premise for any gate, re-authoring, or re-design; the re-scope keeps every synonym-phrased item scored.", "backing_ref": "data/nlb-phrasings-l3a/audit-recoverability.json sha256 d6365bd95e7d61a1cce7585bb446aa8f905b2b8eec08d0756a446e2e70a09bf5 (rel_synonym_only_misses); docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.3", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "The l3a-parse run measures the covered-exact rate and the label-verbatim vs paraphrase stratification directly; whatever it returns supersedes this band. An INCONCLUSIVE landing re-opens FK-NLB-2 with data per ASM-0141; a FAIL routes to parser investment per the frozen kill text."}
165:{"id": "ASM-0620", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB post-outcome-registration disclosure (downgrades the outcome-blindness framing of ASM-0424/ASM-0480 for the l3a-parse/a5-nl pair): the 0847ce0 mapper-parse diagnostic disclosed scored-outcome information (the two FK-NLB-10 dropped families all abstained - unique-maker 43/43 refused, 0 wrong - and in-scope wrong = total wrong = 8) BEFORE the ASM-0480 enrichment ratification and the final scorer/record pins. Every scorer-side edit ratified after that commit (the ASM-0480 enrichment; the design-doc 14.8 round-2 hardening) is therefore POST-OUTCOME-DISCLOSED, and the pair's freeze is post-outcome registration with respect to those disclosed quantities. The previously claimed 'the same edit would be ratified under every possible outcome' counterfactual is WITHDRAWN as unenforceable and relied on nowhere. Lawfulness rests only on the disclosed terms: (i) the FK-NLB-10 carve-out and the enrichment schema requirement pre-date the diagnostic in the commit record (924bf6b before 0847ce0, independently confirmed by the round-2 skeptic); (ii) front-end, phrasing and eval bytes were pinned pre-diagnostic and are G7-enforced at analysis time; (iii) the pipeline is deterministic, so no selection-among-stochastic-outcomes channel exists; (iv) the independent skeptic re-attack gate and the maintainer veto remain the final control. Residual designer-knowledge risk is disclosed, not claimed zero.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md sections 14.5, 14.7, 14.8 item 1; poc/nlb-skeptic/skeptic-output.txt finding 1; commits 924bf6b + 0847ce079189b4d1244911fe026b0799e1db4da7", "rationale": "The independent round-2 skeptic showed the outcome-invariance claim was an after-the-fact stipulation, not an enforceable blind constraint; overclaiming an unenforceable constraint would be worse than disclosing the deviation. The register carries the honest epistemic status so the verdict layer and every consumer of these records see post-outcome registration, its bounded channels, and its remaining controls. Revisit condition: none for this pair; any future record wanting outcome-blind scorer amendment must pre-commit its amendment rule BEFORE any diagnostic runs (new ASM).", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
166:{"id": "ASM-0621", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB skeptic-round-2 scorer/lint hardening (extends the ASM-0424 lawful scorer-side edit set by exactly this named, diff-scoped edit set and no other, executed under the ASM-0620 post-outcome disclosure): (1) G0 one-row-per-arm in both pinned analysis scripts - duplicate/retry rows never resolve by log order; a re-run row must EXPLICITLY supersede every row it replaces via a top-level supersedes:[sha256 of the replaced body's sorted-keys JSON]; more than one non-superseded row per arm, or a dangling supersede target, is INSTRUMENT-INVALID in both log orders; (2) G7 harness-pin enforcement - the instrument-emitted pins_observed (engine, kot_code on a5, nlb_instrument.py, nlb_frontend.py, nlb_map.mjs, the parents' corpus digests, the phrasing corpus files eval/dev/dev-entities/probe/manifest, the lint receipt, the kot-corpus-hash/1 recipe string) must equal frozen constants byte-copied from the records on EVERY arm body, fail-closed on a missing pins block or any drift; (3) G5 existence - the deranged-lexicon arm must EXIST with well-formed integer counts over the full planned covered set before collapse is tested; a missing arm, empty metrics or absent n_covered_exact is a broken instrument, never 'perfect collapse'; (4) full counts integrity in BOTH scorers - run-level covered partition (exact+wrong+refused_parse+refused_engine == 600 l3a / 855 a5), run-level control partition (answered+acceptable+other == 270/106, refused_any == acceptable+other, acceptable == strict+parse on the mapper arm), family-key set equality with unexpected families rejected, per-family bucket partition + exact == ok, covered bucket sums == run-level twins, zero covered buckets on control families, non-negative-integer buckets; (5) nlb_lint.py defaults to --arms-profile model, under which a nonempty waived_forced_substring list is itself a blocking finding (green=False); --arms-profile deterministic-r0 is the explicit attestation pinned for this non-model pair, and the committed receipts regenerate byte-identically under it, so all corpus digests are unchanged. All edits are analysis/lint side; no front-end artifact or phrasing byte changes; no endpoint, threshold, or planned n moves.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.8 items 3-6 and 11; poc/nlb-skeptic/skeptic-output.txt findings 3-6 and 11 (findings 3, 5 and part of 6 empirically reproduced); analysis/l3a_parse.py + analysis/a5_nl.py --selftest fixtures covering each failure mode including the reproduced cases", "rationale": "The reproduced failures showed the previous scorers could admit order-dependent duplicate outcomes, treat an absent scramble control as perfect collapse, and accept mutually inconsistent count claims, while the emitted harness pins were prose rather than gates; each hardening converts a claimed invariant of design-doc sections 6.3/14.7 into an executable fail-closed check with a selftest fixture on the exact reproduced case. Revisit condition: a successor record with a model-based arm must re-derive its own lint-profile decision (the deterministic-r0 attestation is unlawful there per ASM-0423).", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
