     1	#!/usr/bin/env python3
     2	"""nlb_instrument — NL-boundary run (records l3a-parse / a5-nl, DRAFT).
     3	
     4	    python3 tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_instrument.py --vertical l3a --mock
     5	    python3 tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_instrument.py --vertical a5 \
     6	        --arm mapper-parse --phrasings data/nlb-phrasings-a5/eval.jsonl \
     7	        [--phase final]
     8	
     9	RAW OUTPUT ONLY (P2 section 2.4): emits one kot-log/1 record BODY (counts,
    10	pins, config) on stdout; renders NO verdict and knows nothing about the
    11	pre-registered thresholds (DRAFT records registry/experiments/l3a-parse.json
    12	and a5-nl.json; applied by verdict-gen through the pinned analysis scripts).
    13	
    14	Arms (design doc docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 6.4):
    15	  mapper-parse      the pipeline under test: gazetteer + mapper a1-hybrid +
    16	                    closed frame layer (nlb_frontend) -> byte-identical engine.
    17	  gold-replication  measured-ceiling arm: the parent's FULL gold eval (incl.
    18	                    malformed) on the byte-identical engine — instrument gate
    19	                    G2 requires the parent-perfect outcome.
    20	  deranged-lexicon  scramble control (gate G5): seed-0 fixed-point-free
    21	                    rotation of concept bindings (nlb_map.mjs) and, on the a5
    22	                    vertical, of the relational-op bindings (nlb_frontend).
    23	  abstain-all       trivial policy: refuses every phrasing.
    24	  answer-all        trivial policy: never refuses; parses, then fabricates
    25	                    deterministically wherever the pipeline would refuse.
    26	
    27	Scoring (pre-declared, design doc section 6): the NL leg uses the INCLUDED
    28	slice (malformed stratum excluded, FK-NLB-5). Covered exact is scored EXACTLY
    29	as the frozen parents (answer + expected value + provenance in world store +
    30	non-empty license; provenance required on mapper-parse/deranged/gold arms).
    31	Control 'acceptable' refusal = expected engine ERR_* code OR ERR_PARSE
    32	(FK-NLB-6); strict engine-code match reported alongside. The fail-closed
    33	split reports covered wrong-answers (dangerous, gated S2) separately from
    34	refusals (safe), with ERR_PARSE stage tags for stage indictment.
    35	
    36	Deterministic: no RNG anywhere; the full pass runs TWICE and is byte-compared
    37	(metrics.deterministic_repeat_identical). --mock uses quarantined scaffold
    38	phrasings (gen_mock_phrasings) and asserts MECHANICS ONLY ($0, no freeze).
    39	"""
    40	
    41	import argparse
    42	import hashlib
    43	import json
    44	import os
    45	import platform
