Both freeze dry-runs pass, but that check exposed a separate integration seam I’m validating now: the scorers’ new `supersedes` field must also be legal in the hash-chained log schema, otherwise the advertised retry path exists only in unit-test dictionaries. I’m also running both lint profiles and both scorer selftests.
exec
