-        {"claim": "stand-in rationale: the frozen g9 record requires g9.review to be a blinded HUMAN review (GATE-H, ~4h); that human is unavailable at run time and the maintainer requested blind-LLM stand-ins for the outstanding human annotation passes (2026-07-10) so experiments run now and are human-verified later; this record is the SEPARATE, clearly-labelled stand-in on the f2b-transfer-llmproxy model — a fresh id, never a correction of g9; registered as ASM-0550 and ASM-0520", "tag": "STIPULATED"},
-        {"claim": "judge choice: cross-vendor is mandatory because the judged artifacts are Fable-authored (design-vs-judge separation); gpt-5.6-sol effort low under npx-pinned codex-cli 0.144.1 is the established pinned blind-judge mechanism (availability + invocation semantics MEASURED at the truthstyle-2x2 staging, 2026-07-10); registered as ASM-0520 and ASM-0551", "tag": "STIPULATED"},
-        {"claim": "metric operationalisation: substitutability and cross-translatability are rendered as per-sheet blind yes/no/cannot-say judgments from the sheet bytes only; if the human g9.review operationalises the published metric definitions differently (e.g. translation-based cross-translatability), the proxy legs are form-analogous only; composite = MEASURED mechanical legality AND both judged legs; registered as ASM-0521", "tag": "STIPULATED"},
-        {"claim": "severity-comparability: the proxy judge's strictness is uncalibrated to the published DeepNSM evaluation protocol, so clearing (or missing) the +0.10 margin vs the published 0.24 point is form-preserving only and cannot bear on HS-A; direction unproven; registered as ASM-0522, load_bearing false, resolved by the human g9.review on identical sheets", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION"},
