Concrete mechanism: ASM-0422’s rationale still says 27 existing plus 33 fresh, and ASM-0425’s live claim still says 9/27, even though both records cite those assumptions ([assumptions](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/registry/assumptions.jsonl:113)). No corrected successor assumption is cited.

Why it matters: Calling these lines append-only history does not make the still-open, still-cited registered statements true. The artifact is unambiguous, so the registry should carry a mechanical superseding correction.

